<br>
Charm is not over powered.  It's the abilities enchanters have to augment its use that, in tandem with charm spells, makes the ability overpowered.  You have to look at the big picture and understand that charming for a mage, a traditionally defenseless class, is for the most part a death wish when it wears off.  However, for enchanters the risk is not nearly as great because of the rune, root, stun, fear, etc. defensive abilities they have.<br>
<br>
The mage charm spell is a perfect example of a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>situational</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ability that has a huge payoff, but at enormous risk. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.dark-bane.com/mageloframes/sambusframe.htm">Sambus Veneficus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
