<br>
I simply wasn't clear in my post.  I meant that more than a few mages have ranted and raved on this board about how awesome charm is for other classes.  There's been a tendency to overstate the powers of others while understating our own.<br>
<br>
For example, the druid I teamed with who charmed PoD rats had a nice tool at his disposal...but I matched his power by nuking to my heart's content and cannipetting the mana back in very short order.  I was envious of his pet and he was envious of my seemingly endless supply of mana.<br>
<br>
It would appear that our new elemental charming ability can be quite awesome.  It's also balanced by how disastrous it can be to a solo mage when it breaks.  So the other charming classes may be better at it.  But I don't think it makes them better than us in the big picture.<br>
<br>
